string.name: start modeler wizzard
string.value:
In the TopDown or Project Approach you will be working as a project team whereby the organization is first defined in a org tree and the project scope in a process tree.
Preparations and communication are done by a project manager and you will be assigned certain process Flows to work on with others.

string.name: menu bar topbar
string.value: Your current Project you are working with

string.name: start modeler wizzard
string.value:
You see a new Organization Tree Diagram. Draw new Organisation Items from the Toolbar.

You can also create new Diagrams by using the Menubar (File > New).

To use existing Diagram Objects open the Sidebar on the left and goto the Organizations Panels.

You can also create new Diagrams by selecting on an existing Company or Departement and push the "Drill Down" Button. That way there is automatically a Parent-Child Relation between the Diagrams. To model that relation manually you goto the Toolbar and press the Save disk (crtl+s) and choose a Parent Object.

string.name: start modeler wizzard
string.value:
Make sure all your Organisation Items in the Tree have a connection to the Parent Object. You can easily draw relations in a diagram by using the Connector-Tool from the Toolbar.

If you would like to do a Report based on your model, make sure to enter the Properties for each Org.-Item in the Property Editor. The Property Editor can be found in the Sidebar on the right Side.
